    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors were assessed; all seven show achieved levels below required levels for MRL 5. Six factors were not assessed and represent epistemic gaps. The primary claim of model credibility for absolute NIH prediction is stated in prose supported by references to mesh convergence, experimental comparison, and Monte Carlo UQ activities. The assessment package is accepted as a complete submission for regulatory review, noting that the overall V&V credibility determination is Not Accepted due to unresolved gaps across all assessed factors.",
